# Insights & Recommendations

## Key Findings

### 1. Revenue Concentration
A relatively small percentage of customers generate a large portion of total revenue. This indicates that the business relies heavily on high-value customers and retention strategies should focus on these segments.

### 2. Repeat Customer Value
Repeat customers contribute a significant share of total revenue, suggesting that customer retention efforts may be more valuable than focusing only on new customer acquisition.

### 3. Seasonal Demand Patterns
Revenue trends show clear seasonal spikes, particularly during peak shopping periods. This indicates opportunities to align marketing campaigns and inventory planning with seasonal demand.

### 4. Category Performance
A small number of product categories generate the majority of revenue. Prioritizing these categories for promotions and expansion could increase overall profitability.

### 5. Geographic Revenue Distribution
Revenue is concentrated in a few core markets. This suggests opportunities to explore growth in underperforming regions while continuing to support strong markets.

## Business Recommendations

• Develop targeted retention campaigns for high-value and repeat customers  
• Prioritize promotions around peak seasonal demand periods  
• Focus inventory and marketing efforts on top-performing product categories  
• Explore opportunities to expand revenue in underperforming geographic markets
